Package calculator

Class CalculatorAdvancedTest

java.lang.Object
calculator.CalculatorAdvancedTest
@DisplayName("CalculatorAdvanced class test") class CalculatorAdvancedTest extends Object
Testing class used to fully test the code in the CalculatorAdvanced class. It used parameterized test and Hamcrest matchers.

2021-03-30

    • testCalculateAdvanced

      @ParameterizedTest @MethodSource("calculateAdvancedParameters") public void testCalculateAdvanced(double currentValue, char action, double result) throws calculator.exception.NotSupportedOperationException, calculator.exception.NumberNotInAreaException
      Tests the factorial and exponentiation calculation for the calculateAdvanced(char) method, parameterized to take parameters from calculateAdvancedParameters() method.
      Parameters:
      currentValue - is a value that will be stored as a calculators current value.
      action - is a value used to distinguish between factorial and exponentiation calculation.
      result - is the expected result for the calculation.
      Throws:
      calculator.exception.NotSupportedOperationException
      calculator.exception.NumberNotInAreaException

    • testHasCharacteristic

      @ParameterizedTest @MethodSource("hasCharacteristicParameters") public void testHasCharacteristic(double currentValue, char parameter, Boolean result) throws calculator.exception.NotSupportedOperationException, calculator.exception.NumberNotInAreaException
      Tests the hasCharacteristic(char) method by checking if the given numbers are Armstrong or Perfect, parameterized to take parameters from hasCharacteristicParameters() method.
      Parameters:
      currentValue - is a value that will be stored as a calculators current value.
      parameter - is a value used to distinguish between Armstrong or Perfect number check.
      result - is the expected result for the calculation.
      Throws:
      calculator.exception.NotSupportedOperationException
      calculator.exception.NumberNotInAreaException
